problem:
Part of the graph of $f(x) = ax^3 + bx^2 + cx + d$ is shown. What is $b$?

[asy]
unitsize(1.5 cm);

real func(real x) {
  return((x + 1)*(x - 1)*(x - 2));
}

draw(graph(func,-1.1,1.5));
draw((-1.5,0)--(1.5,0),Arrows(6));
draw((0,-1)--(0,2.5),Arrows(6));

label("$x$", (1.5,0), E);
label("$f(x)$", (0,2.5), N);

dot("$(-1,0)$", (-1,0), SE, fontsize(10));
dot("$(1,0)$", (1,0), SW, fontsize(10));
dot("$(0,2)$", (0,2), NE, fontsize(10));
[/asy]

solution:
We have that
\begin{align*}
x^2 - y^2 &= (x + y)(x - y) \\
&= 2 \cdot 2001^{1002} \cdot (-2 \cdot 2001^{-1002}) \\
&= \boxed{-4}.
\end{align*}

